-- Stockton, Ambac Agree to Cap Payments on $21.6 Million of Debt
-- B y   S t e v e n   C h u r c h
-- 2013-02-26T19:26:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-02-26/stockton-ambac-cap-payments-on-21-6-million-in-city-debt-1-.html
The city of Stockton,  California ,
due in  bankruptcy court  today to face creditors, settled a
dispute with Ambac Assurance Corp. by capping payments on $21.6
million in debt, officials said in a statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
